It can be located in the Pacific Rim on the map. Majuro is in the
southeastern corner of the group of islands. - Mod.LL]
******
[2] Turkey (Mus)
Date: Tue 13 Mar 2007
From: Brent Barrett <salbrent@sbcglobal.net>
Source: NTV-MSNBC [edited]
<http://www.ntvmsnbc.com/news/402542.asp>

At least 70 residents of a village in the eastern Turkish province of
Mus have tested positive for typhus [sic], the outbreak being blamed
on polluted drinking water. [Abdominal typhus is another term for the
bacterial disease typhoid, commonly waterborne; the endemic
rickettsial disease typhus is flea-borne. - Mod.LL, JW]
Among the 70 people from the village of Bascatak, in the Malazgirt
district, who have contracted the infection are 4 teachers and 16 students.
Kenan Akpolat, head of the local health authority, said that 400
locals in the village, which has 147 houses, were tested. Akpolat
said that animal waste piled in front of barns has flowed into the
local water supply after heavy rains, causing the outbreak.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The Mus Province is in eastern Turkey as shown in the map (no. 49) at
<http://www.map-of-turkey.co.uk/maps/Turkey.gif> - Mod.LL]
